=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Env_ex27 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark noisy sound, with noise oscillator character around 572 Hz, featuring punchy attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is front_heavy, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: noisy
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: front_heavy

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 572.2584
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0747
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8787
  pitch_clarity: 2.6972
  inharmonicity: 0.7307
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.5947
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Env Example 27
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Env.html
// Tags: Env, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 27 ---
a = Env.adsr;
a.levels;
a.range(42, 45).levels;
a.exprange(42, 45).levels;
a.curverange(42, 45, -4).levels;

(
// Mapping an Env to an exponential frequency range:
{
    SinOsc.ar(EnvGen.ar(Env.perc(0.01, 0.7).exprange(40, 10000), doneAction: Done.freeSelf)) * 0.2;
}.play
)
